caused by the discrete nature of product ion energy levels (e.g., Ryufuku 1980). In practice, since the actual data for such small-$q$ species are usually available 
in the literature, the bias on the scaling relation can barely affect our model. Eq.2 is then used to calculate cross sections for ions that are still missing
in previous publications.




